22/11/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica issued a statement Monday (22 November), reiterating that co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal is mandatory for the republic. 
The prime minister cited a decision to free ten potential witnesses from their duty to keep state and military secrets, as well as the approval given to submitting more documentation requested by the tribunal. 
(B92 - 22/11/04)
